  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

extends java.io.Serializable
    The stack data type operations for a stack.

      • push

        void push(E e)
        Mutator method to push an element to the top of the stack. Precondition: A valid Stack object exists and an element is passed. Postcondition: Element is inserted to the top of the stack.
        Parameters:
        e - Element which is needed to be inserted.

      • pop

        E pop()
throws EmptyStackException
        Mutator method to remove and returns the element at the top of the stack. Precondition: A valid Stack object exists. Postcondition: Element at the top of the stack is removed and returned.
        Returns:
        Element removed from Top of the stack.
        Throws:
        EmptyStackException - Thrown if stack has nothing to pop.

      • peek

        E peek()
throws EmptyStackException
        Accessor method to return the topmost element in a stack without removing it. Precondition: A valid Stack object exists. Postcondition: The topmost element is returned without removing it.
        Returns:
        Element at the top of the stack.
        Throws:
        EmptyStackException - Thrown if stack has nothing to pop.

      • clear

        void clear()
        Mutator method to make a stack empty. Precondition: A valid Stack object exists. Postcondition: Stack is empty.

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Accessor method to check if the stack is empty. Precondition: A valid Stack object exists. Postcondition: It returns true if stack is empty otherwise it returns False.
        Returns:
        True if stack has nothing in it.

      • equals

        boolean equals(StackADT<E> that)
        Accessor method to check if two stacks contain equal items appearing in the same order. Precondition: A valid Stack object exists and a stack is passed. Postcondition: It returns true if two stacks contain equal items appearing in the same order otherwise it returns False.
        Parameters:
        that - Stack which is needed to be compared.
        Returns:
        True if two stacks contain equal items appearing in the same order

      • toArray

        Returns an array containing all of the items in this stack. The top of the stack corresponds to the first element of the array. Precondition: A valid Stack object exists. Postcondition: It returns an array containing all of the items in this stack.
        Returns:
        Array containing all of the items in this stack

      • toArray

        E[] toArray(E[] copy)
        Returns an array containing all of the elements in this list in proper sequence. The runtime type of the returned array is that of the specified array. Precondition: A valid Stack object exists and an array is passed. Postcondition: It returns an array containing all of the elements in this list in proper sequence
        Parameters:
        copy - Array into which the elements of the Stack are to be stored.
        Returns:
        array containing all of the elements in this list in proper sequence

Precondition: A valid Stack object exists and an element is passed. Postcondition: It returns the position of an Element on the stack.
        Parameters:
        e - Element to be searched.
        Returns:
        the position of an Element on the stack

      • contains

        boolean contains(E e)
        Accessor method to check whether a specific element is present in the Stack or not. Precondition: A valid Stack object exists and an element is passed. Postcondition: It returns true if a specific element is present in the Stack otherwise it returns False.
        Parameters:
        e - element that needs to be tested if it is present in the Stack or not
        Returns:
        True if the element is present in the Stack otherwise it returns False.
